## Remarks  
 <span data-ttu-id="62c0f-102">Windows デスクトップ音声は、オブジェクトまたは<xref:System.Speech.Recognition.RecognizedWordUnit> <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.ReplacementText>オブジェクトのコレクションとして認識された語句を返します。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="62c0f-102">Windows Desktop Speech returns recognized phrases as collections of <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.RecognizedWordUnit> or <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.ReplacementText> objects.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="62c0f-103">各オブジェクトは、1つの単語または区切り記号に対応します。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="62c0f-103">Each object corresponds to a single word or punctuation mark.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="62c0f-104">または`DisplayAttributes` <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.DisplayAttributes>のプロパティは、列挙体のメンバーを使用して、指定された単語または句読点の前後で印刷間隔を処理する方法を記述します。 <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.ReplacementText> <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.RecognizedWordUnit></span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="62c0f-104">The `DisplayAttributes` property of a <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.RecognizedWordUnit> or <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.ReplacementText> uses a member of the <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.DisplayAttributes> enumeration to describe how print spacing is handled around a given word or punctuation mark.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="62c0f-105">特定の単語を表示する`DisplayAttributes`方法を指定`OR`するために、列挙体の2つ以上のメンバーをビット単位で結合することができます。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="62c0f-105">Two or more members of the `DisplayAttributes` enumeration may be combined by a bit-wise `OR` to specify how a particular word should be displayed.</span></span>  
  
> [!NOTE]
>  <span data-ttu-id="62c0f-106">音声認識エンジンで使用される表示形式は、言語によって異なります。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="62c0f-106">The display formatting that the speech recognizer uses is language specific.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="62c0f-107">たとえば、によっ<xref:System.Speech.Recognition.DictationGrammar>て提供される既定のシステム文法を使用する認識エンジンへの入力語句は、"Hello コンマ he ピリオド" とします。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="62c0f-107">For example, suppose the input phrase to a recognition engine using the default system grammar provided by <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.DictationGrammar> is "Hello comma he said period".</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="62c0f-108">次に、認識エンジンは<xref:System.Speech.Recognition.RecognizedPhrase> 、次<xref:System.Speech.Recognition.RecognizedWordUnit>の文字列`DisplayAttributes`を含む5つのオブジェクトを含むを返します。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="62c0f-108">Then the recognition engine returns a <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.RecognizedPhrase> containing five <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.RecognizedWordUnit> objects containing the following strings with the following `DisplayAttributes` values.</span></span>  
  
|<span data-ttu-id="62c0f-109">アイテム</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="62c0f-109">Item</span></span>|`DisplayAttributes`|  
|----------|-------------------------|  
|<span data-ttu-id="62c0f-110">こんにちは</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="62c0f-110">Hello</span></span>|<span data-ttu-id="62c0f-111">OneTrailingSpace</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="62c0f-111">OneTrailingSpace</span></span>|  
|<span data-ttu-id="62c0f-112">,</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="62c0f-112">,</span></span>|<span data-ttu-id="62c0f-113">OneTrailingSpace &#124; ConsumeLeadingSpaces</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="62c0f-113">OneTrailingSpace &#124; ConsumeLeadingSpaces</span></span>|  
|<span data-ttu-id="62c0f-114">he</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="62c0f-114">he</span></span>|<span data-ttu-id="62c0f-115">OneTrailingSpace</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="62c0f-115">OneTrailingSpace</span></span>|  
|<span data-ttu-id="62c0f-116">え</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="62c0f-116">said</span></span>|<span data-ttu-id="62c0f-117">OneTrailingSpace</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="62c0f-117">OneTrailingSpace</span></span>|  
|<span data-ttu-id="62c0f-118">.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="62c0f-118">.</span></span>|<span data-ttu-id="62c0f-119">OneTrailingSpace &#124; ConsumeLeadingSpaces</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="62c0f-119">OneTrailingSpace &#124; ConsumeLeadingSpaces</span></span>|  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="62c0f-120">この認識された語句に対して返されるテキストは、"Hello, 彼は言いました。" として出力されます。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="62c0f-120">The text returned for this recognized phrase is printed as: "Hello, he said."</span></span>  
  
   
  
## Examples  
 <span data-ttu-id="62c0f-121">次の例では<xref:System.Speech.Recognition.RecognizedWordUnit.DisplayAttributes%2A> 、オブジェクトの<xref:System.Speech.Recognition.RecognizedWordUnit>リストのプロパティを使用して、単語を語句として書式設定しています。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="62c0f-121">The following example uses the <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.RecognizedWordUnit.DisplayAttributes%2A> property of a list of <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.RecognizedWordUnit> objects to format the words as a phrase.</span></span>  
  
```csharp  
  
// Use the DisplayAttributes property to format speech as text.   
  
static string GetDisplayText(List<RecognizedWordUnit> words)  
{  
  StringBuilder sb = new StringBuilder();  
  
  // Concatenate the word units together. Use the DisplayAttributes  
  // property of each word unit to add or remove white space around  
  // the word unit.  
  foreach (RecognizedWordUnit word in words)  
  {  
    if ((word.DisplayAttributes  
      & DisplayAttributes.ConsumeLeadingSpaces) != 0))  
    {  
      sb = new StringBuilder(sb.ToString().TrimEnd());  
    }  
  
    sb.Append(word.Text);  
  
    if ((word.DisplayAttributes  
      & DisplayAttributes.OneTrailingSpace) != 0)  
    {  
      sb.Append(" ");  
    }  
    else if ((word.DisplayAttributes  
      & DisplayAttributes.TwoTrailingSpaces) != 0)  
    {  
      sb.Append("  ");  
    }  
  }  
  
  return sb.ToString();  
}  
  
```
